. Promises To Revamp Education, And Proffer Solution To Food Security LAFIA – Architect Mohammed Suleiman Awwal, a gubernatorial candidate of the Allied People’s Movement (APM), Wednesday, promised to revamp education and Proffer Solution to food security in Nasarawa if elected as a governor of Nasarawa. Arch. Suleiman Awwal made his plan known shortly after he was declared as the flagbearer of the party through consensus during their party primary held in Lafia, the state capital.. -Advertisement- He explained that if elected as the governor of Nasarawa State he would build technical science schools across the three-zone in order to equip the students with technical skills that would earn them daily. According to him,” what I would do if giving mandate as governor, the first thing to do is to fix education. “Imbibing skills into a child before giving knowledge and allow him to go into the broader way of education is the best, it helps you to have an in-depth knowledge of things. We will ensure that teachers are retrained so as to perform optimally,” he said. Awwal said he would build cottage industries where the teeming youths in the state could be employed after acquiring skills. POLL On agriculture, Awwal said would prioritise three advantage areas; livestock, cereal and locust bean, note that the Nasarawa state has a comparative advantage over other states given her vast arable land. On security, the governorship candidate said he had research on security formula that would address security challenges in Nasarawa state, and noted that he would also employ the service of security experts instead of solely relying on conventional police. “Basically, several factors responsible for insecurity; hunger and deprivation, hunger is the birthday right of anger, no child respect an elder who doesn’t feed him, we will ensure food security and employment.